modules.description: This module defines a partition entry in a GPT (GUID Partition Table), including its GUIDs, LBA range, attributes, and name. It provides functions to construct, serialize, and deserialize partition entries, as well as check if a partition is the all-zero (unused) entry. It operates on `Cstruct.t` buffers for binary encoding and decoding, and uses UTF-16LE zero-padded strings for partition names.

This module handles the construction, serialization, and parsing of GPT headers and partition tables, working with metadata such as LBA locations, UUIDs, and CRC32 checksums. It supports reading and writing partition tables from specific disk sectors and includes functionality to generate protective MBRs. The partition submodule manages individual partition entries, handling GUIDs, LBA ranges, attributes, and UTF-16LE encoded names, with operations to construct, serialize, and validate entries. Examples include creating a GPT structure from a list of partitions, validating GPT headers from disk buffers, and checking if a partition entry is unused.
